#6.Estime um modelo explicativo para sobrevida em Aids contendo as variáveis sexo, idade, tratamento
#e tipo de acompanhamento, utilizando modelo de Cox. Considerando três modelos explicativos
#aninhados.
#Modelo I: sobrevida = idade + sexo
#Modelo II: sobrevida = idade + sexo + acompan
#Modelo III: sobrevida = idade + sexo + acompan + tratam
#1. Faça gráficos de Kaplan-Meier estratificados por cada covariável categórica para verificar
#atendimento ao pressuposto de Cox.
####################################################################################################
ipec <- read.table("ipec.csv", header = T, sep = ";")
names(ipec)
##  [1] "id"      "ini"     "fim"     "tempo"   "status"  "sexo"    "escola" 
##  [8] "idade"   "risco"   "acompan" "obito"   "anotrat" "tratam"  "doenca" 
## [15] "propcp"
ipec$acompan <- factor(ipec$acompan)
ipec$tratam <- factor(ipec$tratam)
KMsexo <- survfit(Surv(tempo, status) ~ sexo, data = ipec)
KMacompan <- survfit(Surv(tempo, status) ~ acompan, data = ipec)
KMtrat <- survfit(Surv(tempo, status) ~ tratam, data = ipec)
par(mfrow = c(2, 2))
plot(KMsexo, lty = c(1, 2), main = "Sexo", mark.time = F)
plot(KMacompan, lty = c(1, 2), main = "Acompanhamento", mark.time = F)
plot(KMtrat, lty = c(1, 2), main = "Tratamento", mark.time = F)

#7. Ajuste cada modelo causal acima utilizando o modelo de riscos proporcionais de Cox, tomando
#o cuidado de interpretar os parâmetros a cada saída. (Lembre de acrescentar o argumento

## Loading required package: ggplot2

### DfBetas ####

ggcoxdiagnostics(modeloIII, type = "dfbeta", linear.predictions = FALSE)
ggcoxdiagnostics(modeloIII, type = "dfbeta",
                 linear.predictions = FALSE, ggtheme = theme_bw())
###Deviance Residuals ########

#Positive values correspond to individuals that "died too soon" compared to expected survival times.
#Negative values correspond to individual that "lived too long".
#Very large or small values are outliers, which are poorly predicted by the model.
ggcoxdiagnostics(modeloIII, type = "deviance",
                   linear.predictions = FALSE, ggtheme = theme_bw())
modeloIII.ggcox=coxph(Surv(tempo, status) ~ idade + I(idade^2)+log(idade), data = ipec)

ggcoxfunctional(modeloIII.ggcox,  data = ipec, point.col = "blue", point.alpha = 0.5)
ggcoxfunctional(modeloIII.ggcox, data = ipec, point.col = "blue", point.alpha = 0.5,
                title = "Graficos Formas Funcionais", caption = "Figura 1")
dresids <- residuals( modeloIII, type="deviance" )
par(mfrow=c(1,1))

lp <- predict( modeloIII, type="lp" )
plot(lp, dresids, xlab="Linear Predictor", ylab="Deviance Residual")
abline(h=2.5, col="red")
abline(h=-2.5, col="red")

###Deviance Residuals ########

#Positive values correspond to individuals that "died too soon" compared to expected survival times.
#Negative values correspond to individual that "lived too long".
#Very large or small values are outliers, which are poorly predicted by the model.
ggcoxdiagnostics(modeloIII.49, type = "deviance",
                 linear.predictions = FALSE, ggtheme = theme_bw())
